zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tsg1665702934527.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsg1665702934527.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsg1665702934527.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tsg1665702934527\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Key Management for DB2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"tsg1665702934527__d6520e17\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Primary and Candidate Keys</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Types of Key Created:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Uniface uses the primary key specification to\n                        create a primary key with <code class=\"ph codeph\">not null</code> specified for the key\n                        fields. <p class=\"p\">Candidate keys are identical to unique indexes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Key Creation:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> The key is created when the table is\n\t\t\t\t created, either on the fly or via scripts generated by the Create Table facility.<p class=\"p\">The SQL statement is issued from within\n\t\t\t\t the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create table</code> statement.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Key Names:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Key names are constructed using the table\n\t\t\t\t name. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7831884\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7831884\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Key Management for DB2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Key Management for DB2 Table 1. Primary and Candidate Keys Types of Key Created: Uniface uses the primary key specification to create a primary key with not null specified for the key fields. Candidate keys are identical to unique indexes. Key Creation: The key is created when the table is created, either on the fly or via scripts generated by the Create Table facility. The SQL statement is issued from within the create table statement. Key Names: Key names are constructed using the table name. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}